The paper discusses privacy-preserving machine learning with homomorphic encryption, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on deep neural networks and their training and inference, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a Keras-like syntax for training and inference, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the efficiency of neural network inference and transfer learning, which falls under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE), respectively.
